    <h2 class="asection">Columnist Comments</h2>

	<div class="item">
				<a href="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/opinion/columnists/lindy-mcdowell/theres-not-much-christmas-cheer-for-our-homeless-16090794.html">
					<img src="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk//editorial//columnistsImages/lindy_mcdowell.jpg" alt="lindy_mcdowell"
						 title="lindy_mcdowell" width="62"
						 height="61"/></a>
				<h4>
					<a href="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/opinion/columnists/lindy-mcdowell/theres-not-much-christmas-cheer-for-our-homeless-16090794.html">
						<span>&#8226;</span>
						There's not much  Christmas cheer for our homeless</a>
				</h4>

				Christmas 2011 and never mind no room at the inn - this year they've even boarded up trade union HQ to keep out the homeless.</div>

		<div class="item">
				<a href="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/opinion/columnists/gail-walker/old-prejudices-have-no-place-in-new-society-16090295.html">
					<img src="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk//editorial//columnistsImages/gail_walker.jpg" alt="gail_walker"
						 title="gail_walker" width="62"
						 height="61"/></a>
				<h4>
					<a href="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/opinion/columnists/gail-walker/old-prejudices-have-no-place-in-new-society-16090295.html">
						<span>&#8226;</span>
						Old prejudices have no place in new society </a>
				</h4>

				<p>
Some people just can't keep out of the news. Take Belfast Lord Mayor Niall O 
  Donnghaile. There he was, busily planning to host a reception for the brave 
  bus drivers who kept us all on the move through the Dark Days of the 
  Troubles.
</p>
</div>

		<div class="item">
				<a href="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/opinion/columnists/ed-curran/anthem-that-divides-ill-at-ease-with-our-goal-of-unity-16089795.html">
					<img src="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk//editorial//columnistsImages/ed_curran.jpg" alt="ed_curran"
						 title="ed_curran" width="62"
						 height="61"/></a>
				<h4>
					<a href="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/opinion/columnists/ed-curran/anthem-that-divides-ill-at-ease-with-our-goal-of-unity-16089795.html">
						<span>&#8226;</span>
						Anthem that divides ill at  ease with our goal of unity   </a>
				</h4>

				If we want a better society, it can't be 'them' and 'us'. It can only be 'all of us'." I raise these words, spoken by the First Minister, Peter Robinson, at his party conference, in the face of two recent controversies.</div>

		<div class="item">
				<a href="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/opinion/columnists/nuala-mckeever/orange-green-and-now-amber-alerts-no-wonder-irsquom-getting-alarmed-16089873.html">
					<img src="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk//editorial//columnistsImages/nuala_mckeever.jpg" alt="nuala_mckeever"
						 title="nuala_mckeever" width="62"
						 height="61"/></a>
				<h4>
					<a href="http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/opinion/columnists/nuala-mckeever/orange-green-and-now-amber-alerts-no-wonder-irsquom-getting-alarmed-16089873.html">
						<span>&#8226;</span>
						Orange, green and now amber alerts ... no wonder I&rsquo;m getting alarmed </a>
				</h4>

				<p>
Last Wednesday, as I was driving along in the car, I heard the BBC weather man 
  tell us that there was an &lsquo;amber&rsquo; alert for the next day. 
</p>
</div>

